postcontent:
I have a small lot of land that was my grandpa's for 40 years, and it's in Wood County, Texas, near Hawkins, in the Land of the Lakes subdivision, Lot 42 in Section A. It's wooded, and it has no improvements. The road it's on is totally unpaved, however, the good news is that you can get to it via the paved county road that runs behind it, if you don't mind hopping over the barbed wire fence. As far as I know, there are no HOA or POA fees on it, only the Wood County taxes that are $2.53 per year.

http://img802.imageshack.us/img802/8007/platbox.jpg - small, lot marked in red
http://img248.imageshack.us/img248/9817/platlarge.jpg - large, unedited
If the above links don't work, email me and I'll send you the pictures.
According to the scale, I would venture the guess that this land is around 40' x 50'. It's to the east of FM 778, south of Opportunity Dr and north of CR 3840 (Slayton Road), the second lot to the left of the one that says 40, underneath the left leg of the letter "A" in "Oakcrest Avenue."

This is about where it is: http://maps.google.com/maps?q=Slayton+Rd,+Hawkins,+TX&hl=en&ll=32.639294,-95.308059&spn=0.00646,0.011362&sll=31.168934,-100.076842&sspn=13.422105,23.269043&oq=Slayton+Rd+Hawkin&t=h&hnear=Slayton+Rd,+Hawkins,+Texas+75765&z=17 and again, there's not really frontage on Slayton Road, there's a strip of land between Slayton and the lot that you have to cross to get to it.

I realize there's not a lot to be done with this land, but it could be your tiny place in the world to call your own, to go camping on, to bury some treasure on... title: For Sale:  S&W MODEL 28-2, WITH BOX
postcontent:
Here's a really nice S&W Model 28-2 in a factory box. The gun is in excellent condition. The box is in very nice condition. The date of manufacture of this is 1966.

There is a story behind this gun. I bought this gun from a lady in Montana who told me that it belonged to her uncle. Her uncle was a bank manager and he bought the gun new and kept it in the drawer of his desk, loaded. When he retired, he took the gun out and shot the six rounds that were in it, cleaned it, and put it away. The box contains five empty casings, along with the original tools that came with the gun. The only mark on the gun is on one sport on the cylinder where it seems that it might have come from being in a wood desk drawer. I've tried to get a photo of it in the last of the gun photos.

Now, the serial number on the box is S 271180. The serial number on the gun is S 275277. The numbers are very close. I have no reason to believe the lady would lie about the gun so my guess would be that when the gun was purchased it was put into the wrong box. In any case, the gun is in excellent condition, and the box and contents are very nice.

Like the kel tec plr16, this is a gun being bought simply for sporting and collecting purposes rather than practical purposes and will end up a tac'd out safe queen among a fairly large collection. I do however understand basic economics, and recognize that prices will be inflated due to the drought. title: For Sale:  Noreen -- Bad s 338 Lapua w/Timney &Picatinny .338
postcontent:
Noreen -- Bad s 338 Lapua w/Timney &Picatinny .338 INCLUDES THE LEUPOLD MARK 4 8.5-25X50 W/TMR AND AMERICAN DEFENSE MFG SCOPE MOUNT AND RINGS,This item is new,It has never been fired NOREEN BAD NEWS .338 Lapua !!!!
Noreen has created the ONLY SEMI-AUTOMATIC .300 WIN MAG and .338 Lapua on the market. The BAD NEWS is a custom-made AR-style rifle that is chambered in the increasingly popular 338 Lapua as well as the powerful 300 WIN MAG. These cartridges give you much greater velocity and power than the typical .308, and as far as ballistics are concerned, the BAD NEWS rifle is going to be the flatter shooting gun for long range shots.The BAD NEWS rifle is a piston-driven semi-auto; this means you can expect greater range and a higher level of reliability by running a cleaner and cooler rifle. The muzzle break on these Noreen’s significantly suppresses recoil. Additionally, the semi-auto nature of the rifle will naturally recoil less than a bolt action because part of the felt recoil is going to chamber the next round. Lighter recoil.This piston-driven system is unlike any other AR-10 on the market. The piston movement is strictly in the action, after the bullet has already left the barrel. This is a huge advantage on a precision rifle compared to conventional piston driven setups found in standard AR's. In those rifles, an LWRC REPR, POF P308, etc. the piston runs parallel to the barrel and moves while the bullet is still in the barrel creating unwanted barrel harmonics which adversely affect accuracy. This rifle's piston is located in the receiver and not along the barrel so the bullet is out of the barrel by the time the piston is working to chamber another round and keep your action cool and clean with no gas ever entering the action.

The semi-automatic will not only give you a much faster follow-up shot, it also allows you to stay focused on your target, optic and the trigger, instead of having to manually operate a bolt-action rifle; all subsequent rounds are chambered by the rifle itself during the gas or blowback operation of the action. The weapon easily disassembles like the standard AR for quick and easy cleaning and reassembly. The piston system drastically reduces fouling, and no venting means no holes for dirt and other contaminants to enter the system.

The next-generation PMAG 30 GEN M3 is a 30-round 5.56x45 NATO (.223 Remington) polymer magazine for AR15/M4 compatible weapons. Along with expanded feature set and compatibility, the GEN M3 incorporates new material technology and manufacturing processes for enhanced strength, durability, and reliability to exceed rigorous military performance specifications.

Modified internal and external geometry also permits operation with a wide range of non Colt-spec platforms such as the HK® 416 and MR556A1, M27 IAR, British SA-80, FN® SCAR™ MK 16/16S, and others. A redesigned bolt catch notch in the rear of the magazine provides increased bolt catch clearance, while an over-travel stop on the spine helps ensure the magazine will not over-insert on compatible weapons.

Similar to the MOE PMAG, the GEN M3 features a long-life stainless steel spring, four-way anti-tilt follower and constant-curve internal geometry for reliable feeding, and simple tool-less disassembly to ease cleaning. In addition, an included pop-off Impact/Dust Cover can optionally be used to minimize debris intrusion and protect against potential damage during storage and transit. Low profile ribs and new aggressive front and rear texture gives positive control of the GEN M3 in all environments, and a paint pen dot matrix has been added to the bottom panel of the body to allow easy marking by the end user for identification. The new, easy to disassemble flared floorplate aids extraction and handling of the magazine while providing improved drop protection, but is slightly slimmer than before for better compatibility with tight double and triple magazine pouches.
